    "content_hash": "f4636201c62899c4",
    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "HEAD OF COMMERCIAL ENABLEMENT \u0026 GTM (NEW VERTICALS)\n\n\nJoin us in our mission to transform the way people shop and eat, where impact, innovation, and growth drive everything we do. Our New Verticals team (Grocery, Retail, and HOP) is the entrepreneurial engine of Deliveroo—tackling complex, real-time challenges to bring everything from daily essentials to high-end retail to our customers' doors. If you are a decisive leader who thrives in informal, fast-paced environments and enjoys turning high-level strategy into scalable action, this is the role for you.\n\n\nWe’re looking for a Head of Commercial Enablement \u0026 GTM to join our Strategy \u0026 Operations leadership. Reporting into the VP of New Verticals \u0026 Consumer, you will own a broad, high-impact remit spanning commercial performance, global launches, and the strategic tech partnerships that power our operational stack.\n\nWhat You’ll Be Doing\n\n\nYou will lead a high-performing team of specialists to ensure our New Verticals business is set up to scale. Your role is the bridge between strategic vision and flawless execution.\n\n - Commercial Enablement: Empower our local commercial teams to outperform. You’ll design initiatives ranging from Joint Business Plans (JBPs) for our most strategic global partners to a world-class L\u0026D agenda that unlocks team performance.\n\n - Go-To-Market (GTM) Leadership: Lead the end-to-end delivery of high-profile launches. Whether it’s integrating Partner Loyalty programs, launching new Dark Store (HOP) sites, or rolling out features like \"Basket Mix\" (combining Grocery and Restaurant orders), you own the governance and execution.\n\n - Policy \u0026 Process Architecture: Define how the business grows. You will design and embed the frameworks that allow for efficient scale, such as Partner Onboarding Playbooks, segmentation frameworks, and restricted items policies.\n\n - Third-Party Tech Strategy: Own the roadmap for our third-party technology ecosystem. You will lead commercial relationships and contract negotiations with middleware providers, catalogue tools, and picking software/hardware partners to ensure they integrate seamlessly into our product stack.\n\n - Senior Stakeholder Management: Provide clear visibility on program health to senior leadership, proactively unblocking teams to bring innovation to market at pace.\n\n\nQualities We’re Looking For\n\nOur ideal candidate is a structured operator with a heavy commercial bias:\n\n - Decisive \u0026 Influential: You move from strategy to action quickly. You have the confidence to mobilize cross-functional teams and the seniority to influence executive stakeholders.\n\n - Commercial \u0026 Collaborative: You build trusted relationships across Product, Strategy, and Commercial teams, ensuring all initiatives deliver measurable business impact.\n\n - Highly Structured: You can run multiple complex workstreams in parallel, maintaining rigour and high standards without losing sight of the ultimate outcome.\n\n\nYour Profile\n\n - Experience: 6–10 years in a commercially or operationally focused role, ideally within high-growth e-commerce, marketplaces, or logistics.\n\n - Execution Track Record: Proven ability to own complex initiatives from the \"blank slide\" strategy phase through to operational rollout.\n\n - Adaptability: You thrive in changing environments where priorities evolve and speed is a competitive advantage.\n\n - Ownership Mindset: You are a \"builder\" who is excited to continuously improve processes and scale a global business.\n\nWhy Deliveroo?\n\nOur mission is to transform the way you shop and eat, bringing the neighbourhood to your door by connecting consumers, restaurants, shops and riders. . We are transforming the way the world eats and shops by making access to food and products more convenient and enjoyable.\n\n\nWe give people the opportunity to buy what they want, as they want it, when and where they want it.\n\nWorkplace \u0026 Diversity\n\nAt Deliveroo, we know that a great workplace reflects the world around us and that true diversity and inclusion make us stronger, more creative, and better at what we do. We’re committed to fostering an environment where everyone can do their best work and feel they belong.\n\nWe believe in equality of opportunity and welcome candidates from all backgrounds regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, socio-economic background, religion, or belief.\n\nIf you have a disability or long-term health condition and need support to apply for one of our roles, or require any reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, you’ll have the opportunity to let us know once you’ve submitted your application. We’ll share details on how to request support so we can ensure you have a fair and equitable experience.\n\nIf you’re excited about making a real impact in a fast-moving marketplace and growing your career alongside ambitious, supportive teams, we’d love to hear from you!",
    "employment_type": "Contract",
